# Assertion Best Practices

## 1. Always Use await with Web-First Assertions

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong - will fail
expect(page.locator('h1')).toBeVisible();

// ✅ Correct
await expect(page.locator('h1')).toBeVisible();
```

## 2. Use Specific Assertions

```typescript
// ❌ Too generic
const text = await page.locator('h1').textContent();
expect(text).toBe('Welcome');

// ✅ Use web-first assertion
await expect(page.locator('h1')).toHaveText('Welcome');
```

## 3. Prefer Multiple Specific Assertions

```typescript
// ❌ One assertion, less information on failure
await expect(page.locator('form')).toBeVisible();

// ✅ Multiple assertions, better debugging
await expect(page.locator('form')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.locator('form input[name="email"]')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.locator('form button[type="submit"]')).toBeEnabled();
```

## 4. Use Soft Assertions for Multiple Checks

```typescript
// When checking multiple things that should all be present
await expect.soft(page.locator('.header')).toBeVisible();
await expect.soft(page.locator('.content')).toBeVisible();
await expect.soft(page.locator('.footer')).toBeVisible();
// See all failures at once
```

## 5. Add Context to Assertions

```typescript
await expect(
  page.locator('.success-message'),
  'Success message should appear after form submission'
).toBeVisible();
```

## 6. Use Negative Assertions Appropriately

```typescript
// Check modal is not present
await expect(page.locator('.modal')).not.toBeVisible();

// Check no error messages
await expect(page.locator('.error')).toHaveCount(0);
```

## 7. Adjust Timeouts for Specific Needs

```typescript
// Fast operation
await expect(page.locator('.instant')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 1000 });

// Slow operation
await expect(page.locator('.slow-load')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 30000 });
```
